Scaling efficiency formula: Speedup = N/(1+(N-1)*r)
@sec-distributed-training-systems-systems-physics-scaling-amdahls-law-communication-4d7f (?@fig-scaling-tax code, line 1124)
“speedup = N / (1 + (N - 1) * sc[‘r’])” with r=0.05 (compute-bound) and r=0.50 (bandwidth-bound)


